# Infrastructure Rules

> Подробная документация по инфраструктуре, деплою и Docker: `docs/deployment.md`

## File Structure

```
├── docker-compose.yml  # Orchestration
├── Dockerfile          # Image build
├── .env-example        # Environment template
├── build.sh            # Build & export script
├── start.sh            # Startup helper
├── DEPLOY.md           # Server installation guide
├── requirements.txt    # Python dependencies
├── docs/               # Documentation
├── scripts/            # Utility scripts
├── tests/              # Tests
└── app/                # All Python source code
    ├── main.py              # Entry point (Starlette + pybotx)
    ├── config.py            # Configuration
    ├── keyboards.py         # UI elements
    ├── states.py            # FSM states
    ├── routes.py            # HTTP endpoints
    ├── logging_config.py    # Loguru setup
    ├── handlers/            # Bot command handlers
    ├── services/            # Business logic (CRUD, domain operations)
    ├── database/            # Models, DB init, auto-migrations (migrations.py)
    ├── fsm/                 # FSM middleware & storage (Redis primary, SQLite fallback)
    └── utils/               # Helper functions
```

## Security

- NEVER commit `.env` files
- Use `.env-example` as template
- Store secrets in environment variables only
- Build images only on trusted machines with internet
